spec: socket_extra173
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra172.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket/__AddressFamily/__SocketKind/__gaierror/__herror __mro__.__len__() values (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra171.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__name__/__package__/__spec__/__loader__ module-level identity and socket.socket.__dict__ accept/close/detach/fileno membership (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra170.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AF_UNIX/__SOCK_RAW enum constants and SOL_SOCKET/__SO_REUSEADDR plain int constants (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra169.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__dict__ connect/makefile/sendfile membership and __dict__.__len__()==28 (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra167.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.AddressFamily/__SocketKind __name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__=='IntEnum' and name lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra165.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.error/__timeout/__gaierror/__herror class identity (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra159.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.socket.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__=='socket' and socket.__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra172."
    - "Wave 354 theme: socket.socket class MRO — socket.socket.__name__=='socket' (len=6); socket.socket.__module__=='socket' (len=6); socket.socket.__mro__.__len__()==3; socket.timeout.__name__=='TimeoutError' (len=12); socket.timeout.__module__=='builtins' (len=8); socket.error.__name__=='OSError' (len=7); socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__=='AddressFamily' (len=13). socket_extra159 anchors socket.socket.__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__; socket_extra165 anchors socket.error/__timeout class identity; socket_extra172 anchors socket.socket.__mro__.__len__()==3 and AF class names. This spec anchors socket.socket.__name__/__module__ lengths and socket.timeout.__name__/__module__ and socket.error.__name__ and socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ lengths as primary novel content under socketclass173."
    - "socket.socket.__name__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. 'socket'=6 chars. socket_extra159 anchors this."
    - "socket.socket.__name__.__len__() == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__module__ == 'socket'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. 'socket'=6 chars. socket_extra159 anchors this."
    - "socket.socket.__module__.__len__() == 6. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.socket.__mro__.__len__() == 3. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. MRO: (socket.socket, _socket.socket, object). socket_extra172 anchors this."
    - "socket.timeout.__name__ == 'TimeoutError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. 'TimeoutError'=12 chars. socket.timeout IS the built-in TimeoutError class — it is an alias."
    - "socket.timeout.__module__ == 'builtins'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. 'builtins'=8 chars. socket.timeout is a builtin class aliased into the socket module."
    - "socket.error.__name__ == 'OSError'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. 'OSError'=7 chars. socket.error IS OSError — a direct alias."
    - "socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0. 'AddressFamily'=13 chars. socket_extra167 anchors AddressFamily class identity."
    - "Note: socket.socket.__name__ == 'socket' and socket.socket.__module__ == 'socket'. Both the class name and module name are 'socket' (6 chars). This is a rare case where a class and its containing module share the same name exactly. socket.__name__.__len__()==6 == socket.__module__.__len__()==6."
    - "Note: socket.timeout.__name__ == 'TimeoutError' (12 chars). socket.timeout is an alias for the built-in TimeoutError exception, which inherits from OSError. The __name__ attribute reveals the true class name 'TimeoutError', not 'timeout'. socket_extra165 anchors socket.timeout class identity."
    - "Note: socket.timeout.__module__ == 'builtins' (8 chars). Since socket.timeout IS the built-in TimeoutError, its __module__ is 'builtins' (the Python builtins module), not 'socket'. This distinguishes it from socket-specific exceptions like gaierror and herror whose __module__ is 'socket'."
    - "Note: socket.error.__name__ == 'OSError' (7 chars). socket.error is a direct alias for the built-in OSError. socket.error is OSError evaluates to True. The __name__ of socket.error is 'OSError', not 'error'."
    - "Note: socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily' (13 chars). socket.AF_INET is an IntEnum member of the AddressFamily enum. Its integer value is 2. 'AddressFamily'(13) is the longest class name in this spec."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

